f the BASIC group comes at a critical time when the 190 plus countries members to the UN climate convention are set to forge a new global deal to cut emissions in which the rich countries want the emerging economies to take on yet more obligations. The US and other developed countries, in the Doha round of talks, had pushed hard to remove any reference to the existing principles of the climate convention while formulating this new global compact.The four countries also discussed countering the push from the rich world to cut the short-lived greenhouse gases first and look for solutions to the long-lasting carbon emissions much later \u2013 an option that benefits the developed world. It pushes the developing world to take higher obligations now while postponing the cuts in emissions required from the developed world.
