n.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a"More money for the National Adaptation Fund (to address the impacts of climate change) is another ask on the ministry's wishlist," the official said. The ministry wants the finance minister to increase allocation for the fund, which was created in July, to help improve the ability of vulnerable communities to address adverse impacts of climate change. The new fund was capitalised with a budgetary allocation of Rs 100 crore, however, there is a need for much higher quantum of funds given the need to help building resilience of poor communities against climate change.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a
