o their promises. So far their efforts have been terrible.\u201d\u000a\u000aOf India\u2019s total installed power capacity of over 300 GW, about 46 GW is renewable including solar, wind and small hydropower projects.\u000a\u000aWhile Piyush Goyal is working overtime to increase the percentage of renewable sources in India\u2019s energy mix, the minister feels that his initiatives will not disincentivise coal-based power projects.\u000a\u000a\u201cWe need coal-based thermal power to provide stable base load in the grid to support renewable sources of power,\u201d said Goyal. Simply put, to avoid instability in power transmission, coal-based power is required to flow through grids, as renewable energy supply depends on weather conditions.
