sons for unsustainable agriculture in the region. Acknowledging media reports of high suicide rate among farmers for the tenth consecutive year, he said the PM's package, loan waiver and other relief measures had reduced distress levels to certain extent, but the government intended to do more for families and dependants of farmers who have ended their life in desperation. "Besides the compensation amount of Rs 1 lakh, the government may consider providing to the family additional support in form of free seeds, fertilizers etc," said Vikhe Patil.
