VMUMBAI: A small drop in the ocean, but a huge dividend for life on Earth! Though demand is increasing by the day, an initiative by people to go in for energy-efficient appliances has helped the country inch ahead in saving power, thus its generation, and natural resources required for its generation.This little step towards climate change-the global agenda set for reducing carbon emissions affecting the ozone layer-has helped the country avoid the setting up of a 2,868 MW power plant over the last three years and the use of over 20 million tones of crude oil. However, a recent survey doesn't talk about the saving of coal in the process.A review of a bureau of energy efficiency ( BEE ) survey by the national productivity council (NPC) reveals that mainly the sale of energy-saving devices (which are replacing conventional gadgets) from 2009 to 2010 has helped the country avoid the setting up of a 1,363 MW power plant. This is up from 881 MW in 2008-09.In 2007-08, the first year in which the review of the sale of energy-efficient appliances was done, the country had saved 623 MW. Of the total 2,868 MW, the amount saved only due to the sale of star-rated appliances was 2,179 MW.As per BEE's original survey, the amount of power generation savings over the last three years (2007-10) stands at 3,730 MW, against NPC estimates of 2,868 MW. The survey, analyzed in September 2010 and released early this year, claims that the country avoided the use of 22.51 million tones of crude oil for power generation.Top among gadgets which largely helped save power generation are air-conditioners-the most energy-guzzling device. Many people's switch to star-rated ACs helped save 1455.89 MW of the total 2179 MW saved only through the sale of star-rated appliances.The survey is based on data on the sale of star-rated (or energy efficient) appliances like refrigerators, ceiling fans, storage water-heaters, agricultural pump sets, colour televisions and tubelights collected from across the country. Surveyors interacted with stakeholders like generation and distribution companies, residential and commercial consumers and industrial giants.The other device that has helped the country save on power generation is the refrigerator-481 MW was saved as people bought new star-rated energy efficient versions. While the replacement of direct-cool refrigerators has helped save 317.51 MW, new frost-free refrigerators save 163.22 MW.The replacement of incandescent bulbs with fluorescent tubelights has helped the country avoid the generation of 160 MW power, followed by 42.25 MW by the agricultural pumps' energy-efficient models. New colour televisions have avoided the generation of around 26.96 MW as people phased out old sets.The contribution of ceiling fans, water-heaters and distribution transformers stands at 1.69 MW, 4.75 MW and 6.69 MW.Power experts said BEE has a lot to work on replacing water-heaters, ceiling fans and TV sets with energy-efficient versions, as savings on them have not increased much. "Promoting these gadgets, including irons and microwaves, in energy-efficient avatars should be the next campaign now," the experts said.
