entific studies also showed that the net impact of first generation bio-fuels on the environment were negative even though they helped reduce the use of fossil fuels.The UN Framework Convention on Climate Change\u2019s secretariat refused to comment on the issue stating, "In principal, we cannot respond to information from unauthorized, unidentified sources.\u201dFigueres was selected for the post by UN secretary general Ban Ki-moon in April 2010 in a competition where Indian government had also put up its candidate, the then environment secretary Vijai Sharma.
