ught in her village. "Due to heat seven of our 15 goats have died. For water we have to walk to the village tank as the well dries up. The cattle suffer and die. The farmers borrow money and are unable to pay back. And, parents withdraw kids from school.''Rajesh from Gujarat said that drought leads to crop loss. "I was withdrawn from school and sent to work in the carpet industry. I earned Rs 50 a month,'' he said.Holistic Child Development India is a humanitarian organisation and takes up different types of development projects which promote the rights, interests and dignity of children.
